  number =       "3",
  pages =        "155--172",
  month =        aug,
  abstract =     "In this article we explore the strengths and
                  limitations of hypertext for the online presentation
                  of thesauri used in information retrieval.  We examine
                  the ability of hypertext to support each of three
                  common types of thesaurus display: graphic,
                  alphabetical, and hierarchical.  Graphic displays
                  generated by hypertext browsers appear to be inferior
                  to their printed counterparts.  The simple
                  alphabetical display can be easily mapped onto
                  hypertext systems but has the inherent disadvantage of
                  not showing a full hierarchy at the entry point for a
                  term.  Hierarchical displays are well suited to
                  hypertext presentation but do not include definitional
