  year =         "1991",
  volume =       "4",
  number =       "2",
  pages =        "87--108",
  month =        jun,
  abstract =     "The emphasis in most hypertext systems is on the
                  navigational methods, rather than on the global
                  document retrieval mechanisms.  When a search
                  mechanism is provided, it is often restricted to
                  simple string matching or to the Boolean model.  As
                  an alternate method, we propose a retrieval
                  mechanism using Bayesian inference networks.  The
