  year =         "1993",
  volume =       "6",
  number =       "3",
  pages =        "207--212",
  month =        sep,
  bibdate =      "Thu Jun 2 10:04:26 1994",
  abstract =     "Depending on the characteristics of the output
                  device and the specific application, various
                  expectations from halftoned images exist. Good
                  reproduction of average grey values is usually
                  demanded from images intended for visual
                  perception. Because textures can drastically
                  influence the appearance of a binary image, it is
                  desirable to control their occurrence. In this paper
